I disagree.  At no stage did i lose interest in what was going on and i thought the tension was palpable at times. A really good leading performance from Mark Wahlberg and it's good to see Michael Kenneth Williams ( Omar Little from The Wire ) in a big role. If i had to be picky i would say that the three people who Jim owed money to could have been a little bit more menacing and the ending is a little bit confusing ( or that could just be me ! ).  Overall though an entertaining , enjoyable movie.  7 out of 10

Wahlberg plays his character as a whiny sarcastic persona in this film, which was a poor substitute for Caan's intensity in the original.  SPOILER ALERT: Changing the ending was also a crappy move. In the Caan version, he goes off on a dark example of self-destruction. In this silly film, it's "love conquers all", fall in love and run really fast through the street for a long time and your gambling addiction will be cured.
